# shadcn/ui Usage Guidelines

## Overview

shadcn/ui is a collection of beautifully-designed, accessible components and a code distribution platform. It is built with TypeScript, Tailwind CSS, and Radix UI primitives. It supports multiple frameworks including Next.js, Vite, Remix, Astro, and more. Open Source. Open Code. AI-Ready.

**Key Principles:**
- **Open Code**: Components are copied into your project, not installed as dependencies
- **Composition**: Build complex components from simple primitives
- **Distribution**: Components are distributed via a registry system
- **Beautiful Defaults**: Components look great out of the box
- **AI-Ready**: Designed to work seamlessly with AI assistants

## Installation

### Initial Setup

The project uses shadcn/ui CLI for component management. Components are installed via:

```bash
npx shadcn@latest add [component-name]
```

### Project Configuration

Configuration is stored in `components.json`:

```json
{
  "$schema": "https://ui.shadcn.com/schema.json",
  "style": "default",
  "rsc": true,
  "tsx": true,
  "tailwind": {
    "config": "",
    "css": "app/globals.css",
    "baseColor": "slate",
    "cssVariables": true,
    "prefix": ""
  },
  "aliases": {
    "components": "@/components",
    "utils": "@/lib/utils",
    "ui": "@/components/ui",
    "lib": "@/lib",
    "hooks": "@/hooks"
  }
}
```

### Component Installation Paths

- **Components**: `components/ui/`
- **Utils**: `lib/utils.ts` (contains `cn` helper)
- **Hooks**: `hooks/` (if needed)

## Component Usage Patterns

### Basic Component Import

```typescript
import { Button } from "@/components/ui/button"

function MyComponent() {
  return <Button>Click me</Button>
}
```

### Component Variants

Components use `class-variance-authority` (CVA) for variant management:

```typescript
import { Button } from "@/components/ui/button"

function ButtonExamples() {
  return (
    <>
      <Button variant="default">Default</Button>
      <Button variant="destructive">Destructive</Button>
      <Button variant="outline">Outline</Button>
      <Button variant="secondary">Secondary</Button>
      <Button variant="ghost">Ghost</Button>
      <Button variant="link">Link</Button>
      <Button size="sm">Small</Button>
      <Button size="lg">Large</Button>
      <Button size="icon">Icon</Button>
    </>
  )
}
```

### Composition Pattern

Components are designed to be composed together:

```typescript
import { Card, CardHeader, CardTitle, CardDescription, CardContent } from "@/components/ui/card"
import { Button } from "@/components/ui/button"

function CardExample() {
  return (
    <Card>
      <CardHeader>
        <CardTitle>Card Title</CardTitle>
        <CardDescription>Card description</CardDescription>
      </CardHeader>
      <CardContent>
        <Button>Action</Button>
      </CardContent>
    </Card>
  )
}
```

### Customization

Since components are copied into your project, you can modify them directly:

```typescript
// components/ui/button.tsx
// Modify the component directly to customize behavior or styling
```

